Author: Leonardo Dantas [aut, cre], James Bisbee [aut], Arthur Spirling [aut]
Maintainer: Leonardo Dantas <leodantas@princeton.edu>
Description: Sensitivity analysis on regression coefficients to assess how measurement error
    (misclassification) in a binary variable affects the estimated treatment effect.
    It calculates extreme bounds on the coefficient by flipping binary classifications in the data
    and provides both graphical and numerical bounds for robustness checking.
